manpagesection(ENVIRONMENT)

bf(wterm) sets the environment variables bf(TERM), bf(COLORTERM) and
bf(COLORFGBG).  The environment variable bf(WINDOWID) is set to the X window
id number of the bf(wterm) window and it also uses and sets the environment
variable bf(DISPLAY) to specify which display terminal to use.  bf(wterm) uses
the environment variables bf(WTERMPATH) and bf(PATH) to find XPM files.
